               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18401019-name-959" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18401019-name-959" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18401019-name-959" type="surname" value="EVERSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18401019-name-959" type="given" value="GEORGE EDWARD"></interp>GEORGE EDWARD EVERSON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a calico-glazer, and live in Weston-place, King's Cross; the prisoner was in my employ. On the 25th of September, I missed this calico, I accused him of taking it, and he left my house—I went with the policeman to the prisoner's lodging—he was not at home, but I found the property there—when I saw him again in the evening he said he was very sorry, and wanted me to let him go—this is my calico—(<hi rend="italic">looking at it.</hi>)</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I found my wages of 12<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. a week insufficient to</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184010190129"></xptr>
               <p>support my wife and increasing family, and I endeavoured to get some tools to work at home—I took this piece home to try my tools—I did not intend to deprive my master of it.</p>
               <p>
